CLOSE ENOUGH.

08:36.230 --> 08:37.929
MAY YOU DRIVE SAFELY

08:38.000 --> 08:40.070
AND FIND TRUE LOVE.

08:40.130 --> 08:42.000
Announcer:
We now return to
The 27th Annual

08:42.070 --> 08:43.270
<i>Krusty the Clown Telethon</i>

08:43.340 --> 08:44.710
<i>for Motion Sickness.</i>

08:44.770 --> 08:45.740
Tip-a-dee...

08:45.800 --> 08:47.500
( <i>drum roll )</i>

08:47.570 --> 08:50.400
Whoo-hoo! I love you people!

08:50.480 --> 08:53.880
I love my kids!

08:53.950 --> 08:55.420
Poor little guys.

08:55.480 --> 08:57.050
So tragic.

08:57.120 --> 08:58.890
So nauseous.

08:58.950 --> 09:01.590
You should see the bus
they came to the studio in.

09:01.650 --> 09:05.120
( <i>crying )</i>

09:08.660 --> 09:09.760
What's next?

09:09.830 --> 09:10.970
Oh, yeah.

09:11.030 --> 09:14.470
And now, a man who needs
no introduction

09:14.530 --> 09:17.560
"The Chairman of the Company"--
you know who I'm talking about.

09:17.640 --> 09:19.110
Get out here, you <i>gumba!</i>

09:21.440 --> 09:23.810
Krustelah, there's
an old friend backstage

09:23.880 --> 09:25.580
who wants to say hello.

09:25.640 --> 09:27.270
Huh? What?

09:27.350 --> 09:28.380
Man:
I can't believe it!

09:28.450 --> 09:29.480
Man 2:
They've been feuding for years.

09:32.120 --> 09:33.320
Come here, you.

09:33.390 --> 09:34.660
Oh, you old clown, you.

09:34.720 --> 09:36.020
I missed you.

09:36.090 --> 09:38.230
This guy is
a national treasure.

09:38.290 --> 09:40.160
That jerk I got
to replace you,

09:40.230 --> 09:42.230
he isn't fit to hold
your slide whistle.

09:42.290 --> 09:44.420
ALL I CAN BE IS MYSELF.

09:44.500 --> 09:47.000
Krusty, can you ever forgive me
for framing you

09:47.070 --> 09:48.400
and putting you in jail?

09:48.470 --> 09:50.400
Hey, if they ever open
the books on this telethon

09:50.470 --> 09:51.370
I'm right back in there.

09:52.670 --> 09:55.540
THAT SIDESHOW BOB IS
A NO-GOOD SHOW BIZ PHONY.

09:55.610 --> 09:56.940
COME ON, BART.

09:57.010 --> 09:59.010
IF KRUSTY CAN FIND IT
IN HIS HEART TO FORGIVE HIM

09:59.080 --> 10:01.150
SURELY YOU CAN TOO.

10:01.210 --> 10:02.510
Oh, Krusty,
I can't tell you

10:02.580 --> 10:04.590
how much I missed this.

10:04.650 --> 10:05.790
Ha-ha!

10:05.850 --> 10:07.090
Marge:
<i>NOW, ABOUT</i>

10:07.150 --> 10:08.390
YOUR
WEDDING DRESS...

10:08.450 --> 10:10.180
I'M NOT SURE
HOW TO PUT THIS...

10:10.260 --> 10:11.090
WHITE!

10:11.160 --> 10:12.490
WHITE.

10:12.560 --> 10:14.230
AND WHAT WOULD YOU LIKE
FOR APPETIZERS?

10:14.290 --> 10:15.820
OOH, APPETIZERS.

10:15.890 --> 10:17.590
WELL, HOMER, YOU SEEM TO BE
A TRENCHERMAN.

10:17.660 --> 10:19.090
WHAT SHOULD WE SERVE?

10:19.160 --> 10:22.490
WELL, YOU CAN'T GO WRONG
WITH COCKTAIL WEENIES.

10:22.570 --> 10:24.510
THEY TASTE AS GOOD
AS THEY LOOK

10:24.570 --> 10:26.740
AND THEY COME IN THIS
DELICIOUS RED SAUCE.

10:26.810 --> 10:29.380
IT LOOKS LIKE KETCHUP,
IT TASTES LIKE KETCHUP

10:29.440 --> 10:32.210
BUT, BROTHER, IT AIN'T KETCHUP!

10:32.280 --> 10:33.950
WELL, SELMA,
HE MAKES A GOOD CASE.

10:34.010 --> 10:35.320
GET WHATEVER YOU WANT.

10:35.380 --> 10:37.250
IT ALL TASTES
LIKE STYROFOAM TO ME.

10:37.320 --> 10:39.790
SELMA, DEAR, I'M CONFUSED.

10:39.850 --> 10:41.290
WELL, WHEN I WAS A KID

10:41.350 --> 10:43.150
WE WERE PLAYING
WITH BOTTLE ROCKETS

10:43.220 --> 10:45.460
AND ONE SHOT
STRAIGHT UP MY NOSE.

10:45.520 --> 10:48.790
I PERMANENTLY LOST MY SENSE
OF TASTE AND SMELL.

10:48.860 --> 10:52.800
OKAY, WE'VE GOT COCKTAIL WEENIES
AND SWEDISH MEATBALLS.

10:52.860 --> 10:54.930
SELMA, THIS WEDDING IS SPINNING
OUT OF CONTROL.

10:55.000 --> 10:56.570
CAN WE REALLY AFFORD IT?

10:56.640 --> 10:58.410
I'VE ALREADY RUN THROUGH
EIGHT OF THE TEN DOLLARS

10:58.470 --> 10:59.770
THEY GAVE ME
WHEN I LEFT PRISON.

10:59.840 --> 11:02.040
HEY, RELAX.
I TOLD YOU I GOT MONEY.

11:02.110 --> 11:04.010
I BOUGHT STOCK
IN A MACE COMPANY

11:04.080 --> 11:06.110
JUST BEFORE
SOCIETY CRUMBLED.

11:06.180 --> 11:08.350
SELMA, THAT'S WONDERFUL!

11:08.410 --> 11:09.740
I JUST HOPE PEOPLE
DON'T THINK

11:09.810 --> 11:11.740
I'M MARRYING YOU
FOR YOUR MONEY

11:11.820 --> 11:14.960
INSTEAD OF YOUR...
LESS TANGIBLE QUALITIES.

11:16.790 --> 11:20.430
TOMORROW WE'LL BE
MR. AND MRS. BOB TERWILLIGER.

11:20.490 --> 11:21.630
ISN'T IT GRAND?

11:21.690 --> 11:24.820
HEY, BOB, GIVE SOME
OF THAT HONEY THIS WAY.

11:24.900 --> 11:27.740
MMM... MMM!

11:27.800 --> 11:29.470
HOLY FRIJOLES!

11:29.530 --> 11:30.960
WE'VE GOT TEN MINUTES
TILL <i>MacGYVER.</i>

11:31.040 --> 11:32.140
DRIVER, HERE'S A FIN.

11:32.200 --> 11:33.430
GET ME HOME,
AND DON'T SPARE THE WHIP.

11:33.510 --> 11:34.840
WHATEVER YOU SAY, MUM.

11:34.910 --> 11:36.040
( <i>belches )</i>

11:36.110 --> 11:37.240
( <i>door slams )</i>

11:37.310 --> 11:38.150
WHAT DID I MISS?

11:38.210 --> 11:40.980
MacGYVER WAS WEARING A TANK TOP.

11:41.050 --> 11:42.350
DANG.

11:42.410 --> 11:44.340
WHY, SELMA, I THOUGHT I WAS
THE ONLY MAN IN YOUR LIFE.

11:44.420 --> 11:46.450
SIT DOWN AND SHUT UP!

11:46.520 --> 11:49.420
Man:
Thank you, SeÃ±or MacGyver,
you saved our village.

11:49.490 --> 11:50.490
MacGyver:
Don't thank me.

11:50.560 --> 11:52.090
Thank the moon's
gravitational pull.

11:56.590 --> 11:59.190
THAT MacGYVER'S
A GENIUS.

11:59.260 --> 12:00.930
FIRST OF ALL,
HE'S NOT A GENIUS.

12:01.000 --> 12:02.400
HE'S AN ACTOR.

12:02.470 --> 12:04.210
AND SECOND:
HE'S NOT MUCH OF AN ACTOR.

12:04.270 --> 12:05.040
YOU'RE LYING.

12:05.100 --> 12:06.500
YOU'RE LYING!

12:06.570 --> 12:08.580
NO, SELMA, <i>THIS IS LYING:</i>

12:08.640 --> 12:11.210
THAT WAS A WELL-PLOTTED PIECE
OF NON-CLAPTRAP

12:11.280 --> 12:12.550
THAT NEVER MADE ME
WANT TO RETCH.

12:12.610 --> 12:13.880
NO!

12:13.950 --> 12:14.950
( <i>crying )</i>

12:18.450 --> 12:20.620
HE WAS SO CRUEL.

12:20.690 --> 12:22.660
THE THINGS HE SAID--

12:22.720 --> 12:24.830
THEY'RE JUST NOT TRUE.

12:24.890 --> 12:26.960
THERE, THERE.

12:27.030 --> 12:28.530
OH, WELL, I GUESS
THE WEDDING'S OFF.

12:28.590 --> 12:30.150
FIDDLE-DEE-DEE.
TOMORROW'S ANOTHER DAY.

12:30.230 --> 12:31.400
BART, STOP THAT!

12:31.460 --> 12:33.260
NO, HE'S RIGHT.

12:33.330 --> 12:34.700
WE'RE A PACKAGE.

12:34.770 --> 12:37.400
LOVE ME, LOVE <i>MacGYVER.</i>

12:37.470 --> 12:39.010
I GUESS THE WEDDING'S OFF.

12:41.370 --> 12:43.200
SELMA, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO SAY.

12:43.270 --> 12:45.140
JUST TELL ME
YOU LIKE <i>MacGYVER.</i>

12:45.210 --> 12:46.410
VERY WELL.

12:46.480 --> 12:49.420
I... I...

12:49.480 --> 12:50.680
I CAN'T DO IT!

12:50.750 --> 12:52.520
EVEN THAT CAR CHASE
SEEMED TACKED ON.

12:52.580 --> 12:54.350
( <i>sobbing )</i>

12:54.420 --> 12:57.090
OH, WOULD YOU TWO KNOCK IT OFF?

12:57.160 --> 12:59.160
I HATE ALL THE PROGRAMS
MARGE LIKES

12:59.220 --> 13:00.520
BUT IT'S NO BIG DEAL.

13:00.590 --> 13:01.660
YOU KNOW WHY?

13:01.730 --> 13:02.600
NO.
GO ON.

13:02.660 --> 13:03.830
WHENEVER MARGE PUTS ON

13:03.900 --> 13:07.300
ONE OF HER NONVIOLENT PROGRAMS,
I TAKE A WALK.

13:07.370 --> 13:09.500
I GO TO A BAR, I POUND A FEW,

13:09.570 --> 13:12.740
THEN I STUMBLE HOME
IN THE MOOD FOR LOVE.

13:12.800 --> 13:14.500
VERY WELL, SELMA.

13:14.570 --> 13:15.770
WHENEVER YOU
WATCH <i>MacGYVER</i>

13:15.840 --> 13:18.050
I'LL TAKE
A VIGOROUS CONSTITUTIONAL

13:18.110 --> 13:20.350
AND RETURN MORE IN LOVE
WITH YOU THAN EVER.

13:20.410 --> 13:22.050
OH, BOB.

13:22.110 --> 13:23.370
BART NO LIKE.

13:23.450 --> 13:24.890
BAD MEDICINE.

13:24.950 --> 13:27.960
( <i>organ playing
"The Wedding March" )</i>

13:28.020 --> 13:29.690
I COULD HAVE BEEN
THE FLOWER GIRL

13:29.750 --> 13:32.120
AND I WOULDN'T KEEP
FALLING DOWN EITHER.

13:32.190 --> 13:34.230
HEY, THEY CHOSE MAGGIE,
OKAY?

13:34.290 --> 13:35.890
YEAH, WELL, IF YOU WANT TO GO
FOR CUTESYNESS

13:35.960 --> 13:38.100
INSTEAD OF COMPETENCE, FINE.

13:38.160 --> 13:40.320
DO YOU, BOB, TAKE SELMA

13:40.400 --> 13:43.840
TO HAVE AND TO HOLD,
IN SICKNESS AND IN HEALTH

13:43.900 --> 13:45.410
TILL DEATH
DO YOU PART?

13:47.310 --> 13:48.410
( <i>gruesome-voiced: )
I DO.</i>

13:48.470 --> 13:49.400
( <i>gasps )</i>

13:49.470 --> 13:51.800
( <i>playing generic lounge music)</i>

13:51.880 --> 13:53.050
MMM.

13:53.110 --> 13:53.850
OH.

13:56.920 --> 13:58.490
HEY, WIENER BOY

13:58.550 --> 14:00.050
WHERE DO YOU THINK
<i>YOU'RE GOING?</i>

14:02.390 --> 14:04.430
( <i>munching and gobbling )</i>

14:06.990 --> 14:10.360
I'M THE ONLY SINGLE GIRL
LEFT IN THE FAMILY.

14:14.470 --> 14:16.470
WELL, I GUESS
IT COULD BE WORSE.

14:16.530 --> 14:18.300
OH, THERE'S
KRUSTY THE CLOWN.

14:18.370 --> 14:19.410
KRUSTY!

14:19.470 --> 14:21.040
KRUSTY, SAY
SOMETHING FUNNY.

14:21.110 --> 14:22.680
OH, GEE, A JOKE, HUH?

14:22.740 --> 14:25.850
UM... UH... FUNNY...

14:25.910 --> 14:27.680
OKAY, THIS GUY WALKS INTO A BAR

14:27.750 --> 14:30.750
AND TAKES OUT A TINY PIANO
AND A 12-INCH PIANIST...

14:30.820 --> 14:31.750
OH, NO, WAIT.

14:31.820 --> 14:33.820
I CAN'T TELL THAT ONE.

14:33.890 --> 14:36.920
DEAR FRIENDS, 41 YEARS AGO

14:36.990 --> 14:41.800
GOD TOOK 168 POUNDS OF CLAY,
AND HE MADE ME A WOMAN

14:41.860 --> 14:44.200
AND FOR THIS,
I THANK HIM.

14:44.260 --> 14:45.800
I JUST WANTED TO SAY

14:45.860 --> 14:48.430
ON THE ADVICE
OF MY NEW HUSBAND

14:48.500 --> 14:50.670
I'VE DECIDED
TO GIVE UP SMOKING...

14:50.740 --> 14:52.410
( <i>cheering )</i>

14:52.470 --> 14:55.010
...EXCEPT FOR AFTER MEALS
AND AFTER <i>MacGYVER.</i>

14:55.070 --> 14:57.430
SELMA, DEAR,
YOU'LL BURY US ALL.

14:59.540 --> 15:00.800
CHIEF WIGGUM
YOU'VE BEEN AROUND.

15:00.880 --> 15:02.620
YOU DON'T TRUST
SIDESHOW BOB, DO YOU?

15:02.680 --> 15:04.750
LIGHTEN UP, SON.

15:04.820 --> 15:06.550
IF HE WAS GOING
TO COMMIT A CRIME

15:06.620 --> 15:09.690
WOULD HE HAVE INVITED
THE NUMBER-ONE COP IN TOWN?

15:09.750 --> 15:11.620
NOW, WHERE DID I PUT MY GUN?

15:11.690 --> 15:12.930
OH, YEAH.

15:12.990 --> 15:15.500
I SET IT DOWN WHEN I GOT
A PIECE OF CAKE.

15:15.560 --> 15:16.900
( <i>cheering )</i>

15:18.660 --> 15:20.520
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO SAY.

15:20.600 --> 15:23.300
JUST TELL ME WHAT YOU
KNOW I WANT TO HEAR.

15:23.370 --> 15:26.470
I'M DYING OF JEALOUSY.

15:26.540 --> 15:28.040
THANK YOU.

15:28.110 --> 15:30.740
( <i>shouting farewells )</i>

15:30.810 --> 15:32.850
THAT'S RIGHT, DEAR.

15:32.910 --> 15:35.050
ENJOY YOUR REST.

15:35.110 --> 15:37.210
THE WEDDING WAS
VERY TOUGH ON YOU

15:37.280 --> 15:39.920
AND THE HONEYMOON
IS GOING TO BE...

15:39.980 --> 15:41.380
MURDER.

15:41.450 --> 15:43.910
( <i>menacing laughter )</i>

15:55.850 --> 15:58.460
Welcome to our video honeymoon.

15:58.520 --> 16:01.190
We're using the video camera
cousin Doug gave us

16:01.260 --> 16:04.090
and the video cassette
Homer gave us.

16:04.160 --> 16:07.630
HEY, AND AFTER WE WATCH THIS,
WE CAN TAPE OVER IT.

16:07.700 --> 16:11.940
There's Shelbyville Falls,
Rolling Rock,

16:12.000 --> 16:14.440
and here's another
breathtaking sight--

16:14.500 --> 16:17.200
my brand-new hubby.

16:17.270 --> 16:19.280
I wanted a room with a fireplace

16:19.340 --> 16:20.610
you brainless luggage monkey!

16:20.680 --> 16:23.050
Like the one in your brochure!

16:23.110 --> 16:24.780
Oh, Selma, dear.

16:24.850 --> 16:28.250
I was just chatting
with my good friend... Dennis.

16:28.320 --> 16:30.050
Now, smile for the camera,
that's a good lad.

16:31.790 --> 16:33.560
( <i>metallic squeaking )</i>

16:33.620 --> 16:35.160
Ah, fire--

16:35.220 --> 16:37.920
scourge of Prometheus,
toaster of marshmallows...

16:37.990 --> 16:40.320
eradicator of dead wood.

16:40.400 --> 16:43.600
Oh, Selma, dear--
you and your little camera.

16:43.670 --> 16:46.000
What do you say we
shut it off for a while?

16:46.070 --> 16:47.340
And make love?

16:49.300 --> 16:50.630
I suppose so.

16:50.710 --> 16:53.180
Marge:
OH, THAT'S SWEET.

16:53.240 --> 16:56.550
WHY WOULD SIDESHOW BOB
GO SO NUTS OVER A FIREPLACE?

16:56.610 --> 16:58.750
BECAUSE HE WANTS
HIS HONEYMOON

16:58.810 --> 17:00.240
TO BE ROMANTIC.

17:00.320 --> 17:02.490
ROMANTIC? WITH AUNT SELMA?

17:02.550 --> 17:04.589
I GUESS YOU'RE JUST
TOO YOUNG TO UNDERSTAND.

17:04.650 --> 17:06.210
HMM...

17:06.290 --> 17:10.390
( <i>Selma moaning )</i>

17:10.460 --> 17:14.500
BOB, ONE OF MY FILLINGS
FELL OUT.

17:14.560 --> 17:17.420
EVEN MURDER
HAS ITS UGLY SIDE.

17:17.500 --> 17:20.740
BOB, WOULD YOU MIND
RUBBING MY FEET?

17:20.800 --> 17:23.069
( <i>shuddering groan )</i>

17:23.140 --> 17:25.410
DARLING, YOU MAKE IT SOUND
LIKE A CHORE.

17:27.240 --> 17:29.010
OOH... OH...
GOOD... MMM...

17:29.080 --> 17:30.280
SOON I WILL KILL YOU.

17:30.350 --> 17:31.080
HUH?!

17:31.150 --> 17:32.550
<i>SON PIEDS SENTIT BEAU--</i>

17:32.610 --> 17:34.480
FRENCH FOR
"HER FOOT SMELLS LOVELY."

17:34.550 --> 17:35.790
OH.

17:35.850 --> 17:37.490
PREPARE TO BE MURDERED.

17:37.550 --> 17:38.360
HUH?

17:38.420 --> 17:40.290
( <i>speaking Sanskrit )</i>

17:40.360 --> 17:43.830
THAT'S... SANSKRIT FOR
"YOUR TOES ARE LIKE PERFUME."

17:43.890 --> 17:44.860
( <i>laughs )</i>

17:44.930 --> 17:46.660
<i>VOY A MATAR A USTED.</i>

17:46.730 --> 17:47.630
WHA..?

17:47.700 --> 17:48.730
THAT'S SPANISH FOR

17:48.800 --> 17:50.600
"I AM GOING TO KILL YOU."

17:50.670 --> 17:51.600
SAY WHAT?

17:51.670 --> 17:52.970
WHY, DEAR,
I DO BELIEVE IT'S TIME

17:53.030 --> 17:54.700
FOR YOUR BELOVED <i>MacGYVER.</i>

17:54.770 --> 17:55.970
OH, HEY, YOU'RE RIGHT.

17:57.470 --> 17:59.110
( <i>suspenseful music )</i>

18:06.210 --> 18:07.910
( <i>metallic squeaking )</i>

18:07.980 --> 18:09.310
WELL, TIME
FOR MY WALK.

18:09.380 --> 18:10.080
MM.

18:10.150 --> 18:11.620
DON'T FORGET TO DIE.

18:12.790 --> 18:14.630
DING-DONG.

18:14.690 --> 18:17.190
I WAS FEELING KIND OF LONELY
WITHOUT SELMA.

18:17.260 --> 18:19.400
MIND IF I WATCH TV WITH YOU?

18:19.460 --> 18:22.030
OH, GO AHEAD, PATTY.

18:22.100 --> 18:24.370
Tonight, on <i>MacGyver...</i>

18:24.430 --> 18:25.570
<i>MacGyver...</i>

18:25.630 --> 18:26.760
<i>MacGyver...</i>

18:26.830 --> 18:27.690
<i>MacGyver...</i>

18:27.770 --> 18:30.170
AUNT SELMA HAS ONE HOUR TO LIVE.

18:30.240 --> 18:31.240
Homer:
HEY, DOWN IN FRONT.

18:35.510 --> 18:36.250
GOODBYE.

18:39.580 --> 18:40.750
( <i>explosion )</i>

18:40.820 --> 18:41.820
( <i>screaming )</i>

18:44.220 --> 18:46.720
FRONT DESK, THERE'S BEEN
A TERRIBLE ACCIDENT IN MY ROOM!

18:48.390 --> 18:49.530
( <i>glass crunching )</i>

18:51.760 --> 18:54.200
POOR SELMA-- YOU WERE HAVING

18:54.260 --> 18:55.730
SUCH A LOVELY EVENING

18:55.800 --> 18:57.870
â™ª ...AND THEN I WENT
AND SPOILED IT ALL â™ª

18:57.930 --> 19:02.200
â™ª BY DOING SOMETHING STUPID
LIKE EXPLODE YOU. â™ª

19:02.270 --> 19:04.510
SIDESHOW BOB, I'M AFRAID
THE ONLY VICTIMS HERE

19:04.570 --> 19:06.970
ARE THE GOOD PEOPLE
AT BEST WESTERN HOTELS.

19:07.040 --> 19:07.610
BART!

19:09.340 --> 19:09.870
SELMA!

19:11.010 --> 19:11.720
OH!

19:11.780 --> 19:12.880
YOU TRIED TO KILL ME.

19:12.950 --> 19:14.480
I WANT A SEPARATION.

19:16.680 --> 19:19.180
MY BEST-LAID PLANS
HAVE <i>GANG AGLEY.</i>

19:19.250 --> 19:20.880
CHIEF WIGGUM, THINK YOU HAVE
ROOM IN YOUR JAIL

19:20.960 --> 19:22.690
FOR A TWO-TIME LOSER?

19:22.760 --> 19:24.700
WELL, NO, FRANKLY,
BUT THAT NEVER
STOPPED US BEFORE.

19:26.960 --> 19:27.970
BART, I MUST KNOW

19:28.030 --> 19:29.730
HOW DID YOU UNTANGLE MY WEB?

19:29.800 --> 19:31.230
YEAH, BART, CLUE US IN.

19:31.300 --> 19:33.800
WELL, I'D HATE TO TELL
THE NUMBER-ONE COP IN TOWN

19:33.870 --> 19:35.240
HOW TO DO HIS JOB.

19:35.300 --> 19:37.600
NO, PLEASE, IT'S
THE ONLY WAY I'LL LEARN.

19:37.670 --> 19:39.110
ALL RIGHT.

19:39.170 --> 19:40.630
<i>SIDESHOW BOB SEEMED
SO DESPERATE</i>

19:40.710 --> 19:42.880
<i>TO GET THAT FIREPLACE, BUT WHY?</i>

19:42.940 --> 19:44.370
<i>THEN IT HIT ME--</i>

19:44.450 --> 19:45.820
<i>THE GAS!</i>

19:45.880 --> 19:48.250
<i>SURELY ANYONE
WOULD HAVE NOTICED A GAS LEAK</i>

19:48.320 --> 19:51.290
<i>EXCEPT AUNT SELMA.</i>

19:51.350 --> 19:54.580
Selma:
<i>I PERMANENTLY LOST MY SENSE
OF TASTE AND SMELL.</i>

19:54.660 --> 19:55.960
Bart:
<i>SHE HAPPILY WATCHED
HER MacGYVER</i>

19:56.020 --> 19:57.180
<i>UNAWARE THAT HER ROOM</i>

19:57.260 --> 19:59.900
<i>WAS SILENTLY FILLING
WITH NATURAL GAS.</i>

19:59.960 --> 20:01.470
<i>ALL IT NEEDED TO EXPLODE</i>

20:01.530 --> 20:05.570
<i>WAS A SINGLE SPARK,
SAY, FROM A CIGARETTE.</i>

20:05.630 --> 20:06.330
Selma:
<i>I'VE DECIDED</i>

20:06.400 --> 20:07.940
<i>TO GIVE UP SMOKING</i>

20:08.000 --> 20:10.030
<i>EXCEPT FOR AFTER MEALS
AND AFTER MacGYVER.</i>

20:10.100 --> 20:11.700
Bart:
<i>HER ONLY HOPE WAS
A PLUCKY YOUNG BOY</i>

20:11.770 --> 20:13.670
<i>AND HIS SLOW-WITTED FATHER.</i>

20:13.740 --> 20:15.750
DAD, WHEN AUNT SELMA
LIGHTS UP HER CIGARETTE

20:15.810 --> 20:16.880
AT THE END OF <i>MacGYVER</i>

20:16.940 --> 20:18.470
SHE'LL BE BLOWN
TO KINGDOM COME.

20:18.550 --> 20:19.250
COME AGAIN?

20:21.780 --> 20:23.180
<i>AFTER TRYING FOUR TIMES</i>

20:23.250 --> 20:25.220
<i>TO EXPLAIN IT TO HOMER,
I EXPLAINED IT TO MOM</i>

20:25.290 --> 20:26.820
<i>AND WE WERE ON OUR WAY!</i>

20:26.890 --> 20:27.920
TO THE SIMPSON-MOBILE!

20:29.960 --> 20:30.690
( <i>tires squealing )</i>

20:45.810 --> 20:46.910
NOOO!!

20:50.650 --> 20:53.480
BUT WAIT, IF YOU SAVED SELMA,
WHY DID THE ROOM EXPLODE?

20:53.550 --> 20:55.720
OH, I'LL FIELD THAT ONE.

20:55.780 --> 20:57.780
<i>ME AND THE BOYS
WERE ALL CELEBRATING
A JOB WELL DONE</i>

20:57.850 --> 20:59.220
<i>WHEN I THREW MY MATCH</i>

20:59.290 --> 21:00.620
<i>IN THE VICINITY
OF THE CRIME SCENE.</i>

21:03.120 --> 21:05.150
OH, RIGHT-- THE GAS.

21:05.230 --> 21:06.400
I'LL BE BACK.

21:06.460 --> 21:07.630
YOU CAN'T KEEP THE DEMOCRATS

21:07.700 --> 21:09.070
OUT OF THE WHITE HOUSE FOREVER

21:09.130 --> 21:11.440
AND WHEN THEY GET IN,
I'M BACK ON THE STREETS

21:11.500 --> 21:13.300
WITH ALL MY CRIMINAL BUDDIES!

21:13.370 --> 21:15.510
( <i>maniacal laughter )</i>

21:19.440 --> 21:22.180
I FEEL LIKE SUCH A FOOL.

21:22.240 --> 21:23.900
WELL, HE FOOLED
ALMOST EVERYONE

21:23.980 --> 21:28.050
BUT THERE WAS ONE LITTLE BOY
WHO NEVER LOST HIS MISTRUST.

21:28.120 --> 21:30.150
THANKS, MOM.

21:30.220 --> 21:32.090
NOW, LET'S GET OUT
OF THIS GAS-FILLED HALLWAY

21:32.150 --> 21:34.110
BEFORE WE ALL SUFFOCATE.

21:34.190 --> 21:36.330
( <i>all laughing )</i>

22:41.560 --> 22:43.330
